HEADWORD: Haranguer
<hw>Ha*rang"uer</hw> <pr>(h⟦adot⟧*r⟦acr⟧ng"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>One who harangues, or is fond of haranguing; a declaimer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With them join'd all th' <qex>haranguers</qex> of the throng,⟦br⟧
That thought to get preferment by the tongue.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

